          <feedbackText>&lt;div&gt;Incorrect. Complete graphs with an odd number of vertices always have Eulerian circuits because every vertex has even degree. In $K_n$ with odd $n$, each vertex has degree $n-1$ (even).&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
