            <domain>MATH</domain>
          </expression>
          <condition id="94">
            <code></code>
            <domain>MATH</domain>
          </condition>
          <result>0</result>
          <feedbackText>&lt;div&gt;Incorrect. A complete graph already has all possible edges you&lt;br&gt;cannot add more. $K_7$ already has an Eulerian circuit because all&lt;br&gt;vertices have even degree.&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;Solution: Yes, because all vertices have even degree&lt;/div&gt;</feedbackText>
        </de.uni__due.s3.jack3.entities.stagetypes.mc.MCFeedback>
